\f0\b \cf0 Color Coding of Scripts
\f1\b0 \
\
Lilt uses the following color coding scheme to indicate the presence of linkable inputs and outputs of a script through the color of the on-off button that bears the scripts name: \
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\f2\i \cf0 Color		Input or Output of the Script
\f1\i0 \
white		no linkable input or output\
blue			audio rate output\
green		control rate output\
red			audio rate input (usually also audio rate output)\
yellow		buffer-number input (uses audio buffers)\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b \cf0 Representation of Outputs and Inputs
\f1\b0 \
\
The output of a script is represented as a small drag-source rectangle marked with the character "o" to the right of that scripts on/off button (a button at the top of the scripts window, bearing the scripts name). Currently there is only one output for each script.\
\
Every contollable parameter of a script is an input. The inputs are represented as drag-sink rectangles at the left of the sliders for controlling the parameters and bearing the parameters' names: \
\
