\f0\b \cf0 Creating Links
\f1\b0 \
\
To create a link between an output and an input, drag the drag-source representing the output from the box marked "o" to the right of a script's on-off button to the drag-sink label representing an input from one of the parameters of another script. The system will only permit dragging to those inputs that are compatible with the output. That is: \
\
1. Inputs that are of the same rate as the output (audio-rate '
\f2\i ar
\f1\i0 ' or control-rate '
\f2\i kr
\f1\i0 ').\
2. Inputs whose linking does not create a cycle in the synth graph. \
\

